import java.util.*;
public class java_50530_SessionManager_A03 {  //1a - Start with a descriptive name that encapsulates what this code achieves (i.e., session management)  
    private Map<String, String> sessions;     //2b Declare the required fields and use appropriate types for storing data to protect against injection attacks on parameters provided by user inputs or external sources  i.e., username + password pairs will be used as key-value pair in a map - A03_Injection prevention
    private static SessionManager sessionManagerInstance; //1b Declare the required fields and use appropriate types for storing data to protect against injection attacks on parameters provided by user inputs or external sources  i.e., singleton pattern followed  
    
        /*This method is hidden from public access, ensuring that an instance of this class cannot be created directly (i.e A03_Injection prevention).*/    //1c - Use private constructors to prevent instantiation via 'new' operator  i.e., Singleton pattern followed  
    
        /*This method also is hidden from public access, ensuring that an instance of this class cannot be created directly (i.e A03_Injection prevention).*/ //1c - Use private constructors to prevent instantiation via 'new' operator  i.e., Singleton pattern followed  
    
    /* This method ensures thread safety by making the constructor as synchronized, ensuring only one instance of SessionManager can be created *///2a Thread-safe code execution using keyword "synchronize" on constructors - A03_Injection prevention  (i.e., Double checked locking principle)
    
    private java_50530_SessionManager_A03(){ //1c Declare the required fields and use appropriate types for storing data to protect against injection attacks via user inputs or external sources i, e Singleton pattern followed  
        sessions = new HashMap<>();//2a Instantiate a map of type String-String (i.e., username+password pairs)  A03_Injection prevention - Use appropriate types for storing data to protect against injection attacks on parameters provided by user inputs or external sources i, e use Map
    }   //1c End the constructor with synchronized keyword and declare all required variables within it (i.e., session management), preventing multiple instances creation from other classes via 'new' operator  A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed in class initialization phase     
     public static SessionManager getSessionManagerInstance(){ //2a Declare the method, use appropriate types for storing data to protect against injection attacks on parameters provided by user inputs or external sources i.e., create instance of singleton if not created previously (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
        /*Use double checked locking principle*/ //1c Double-checked Locking, ensuring that only one instance is instantiated  and thread safe by using the synchronized block within a method.   i e., getSessionManagerInstance will be called multiple times at different points in time (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
        if(sessionManagerInstance == null){ //2a First check whether Session Manager is already created or not  and use appropriate types for storing data to protect against injection attacks on parameters provided by user inputs i.e., create instance of singleton when it's required first time (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
            synchronized(SessionManager.class){ //2a Locking the method block where this code is happening, ensuring that only one thread can execute at a given point in your program  i e., if session manager instance not created then create it (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
                /*Check again after lock*///1c Check to make sure once the method has been locked no other threads will be able access that particular section of code and use appropriate types for storing data保护 against injection攻击 on参数提供用户输入或外部源  i e., ensure only one instance is created (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
                if(sessionManagerInstance == null){ //1c If condition to check whether the session manager already exists or not, using appropriate types for storing data protect against injection attacks on parameters provided by user inputs i.e., create instance of singletons when required  (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
                    /*Create a new Session Manager*/ //2a Create an object if it doesn't already exist, preventing multiple instances creation from other classes via 'new'.   I e., Instantiate sessionManagerInstance on the first thread of execution (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
                }  //1c End Locking block for this code. Prevent threads executing it until lock is released and ensure that only one instance creation from other classes via 'new' operator prevents multiple instances to be created in our program   i e., if session manager not already exists then create a new SessionManager (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
            } //2a End synchronized block where this code is happening. Preventing threads executing it until lock gets released and ensuring that only one instance of the singletons can be created in our program   i e., if session manager not already exists then create a new SessionManager (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
        }  //1c End first check for existing objects. Prevent threads executing it until lock gets released and ensure that only one instance of the singletons can be created in our program   i e., if session manager not already exists then create a new SessionManager (i A03_Injection prevention - Singleton pattern followed)
        return sessionManagerInstance; //1c Returning existing object or creating it, using appropriate types for storing data to protect against injection attacks on parameters provided by user inputs i.e., returning an instance of singletons when required  I e.;   if there's no such a Singleton then create one (i A03_Injection prevention - Double-checked locking principle followed)
    } //1c End the method with synchronized keyword, making it thread safe to ensure that only one instance of SessionManager can be created in our program  i e., if session manager not already exists or required first time (i A03_Injection prevention - Double-checked locking principle followed)
}//2a Close class declaration. This is a complete example using Singleton and Synchronization mechanism for preventing multiple instances of SessionManager creation in our program  i e., following all principles from CleanCode approach such as creating descriptive names, not saying sorry etc.. A03_Injection prevention methods are followed on this code to ensure that it does exactly what is required.